Hello Friends!! With the new year in full swing I just wanted to take the opportunity to Re-Introduce myself and tell you a little bit of MY story!

The Just: I am a Fashion Retail expert who has a curated, shop-able fashion collection. I give honest, realistic style tips and fashion advice so you can wear what's best for you with confidence and style.

Everything until now: Where to begin? I have owned and operated a Retail business for the last 18 years. I have had 2 brick and mortars and I have sold everything from makeup, to candles, to skincare and shower caps- Yes, Shower Caps! I was even in business before Social Media can you even believe it?

After closing my first brick and mortar 8 years ago, Blush & Vyne was was born with the goal to continue servicing my incredible community with the focus mainly on Fashion & Accessories. With two little boys at home, I wanted to be closer to home with more flexibility so I found a showroom and hit the ground running.

2 years later something important happened. I experienced a burn out. I was emotionally and physically drained. The rise of Social Media and the fact that it had to become an integral part of my business was a piece that I couldn't really fit into my puzzle- but I knew I had to. 

So I regrouped. I took a break. A Short Break, and focused on my Mental Health and realistic goals, because I knew Blush & Vyne was a success. But as a founder, I needed to refuel and re-calibrate. 

I moved my operations home. I focused on my ecom, my social media, my message and my community. We went through a pandemic together and we grew. We got stronger, smarter and way more fashionable ,together, and there's so much more to come!

More about me:
* I am a 90's chick (music, fashion, culture)
* I have two boys and I am the most Stylish Sports Mom out there
*I started my career in Fundraising and Event Planning
*I will always tell you if something looks bad- I'm too authentic to lie! Which means you will always walk away looking good!
* I always answer my DMs!

So hey! If you are new, welcome, if you are here, I would love to know what you love most about B & V- drop a comment below.
xx- Sidra

Micro needling is Collagen induction therapy that involves repeatedly puncturing the skin with tiny, sterile needles. The damage helps stimulate your skin’s healing process, so it produces more collagen and elastin. These proteins keep your skin firm and smooth.

This is 1 of 3 treatments from @skinenviemedispa that will take place over 3
Months. 

Did it hurt ? Not really. There is an option for numbing cream but I don’t think I would need it next time. 

Is there downtime? By the next day most of the redness was gone and I just had to wait another 24 hours till I could use face makeup and certain products. 

Keep following for the results !

I love the dress but it’s a year and half since I last wore it and I really wanted to “make use of it “. Truth be told, the dress was a bit short (when in Vegas!) and I didn’t feel like myself in it. 

I only packed a few things and wore it anyway but when the night was over, I decided this dress was not for me and I should have listened to my gut! Just because you have it, doesn’t mean it’s right for this particular moment in time. 

Be kind to yourself, your closet and your overall well being. Fashion plays a big part in it so work with it, not against it. And remember, I’m always here to help!
